ECB Sources
===========

 * Source files can be selected by clicking a mouse button (*note Using
   the mouse::) or hitting RETURN (*note Using the keyboard::) on the
   source row in the "ECB-Sources" or "ECB- History" windows.

   IMPORTANT: If you hold down the SHIFT-key while clicking with the
   primary mouse button (*note Using the mouse::) or RETURN (*note
   Using the keyboard::) on a source row in the ECB-Sources or
   ECB-History windows then the source will not be displayed in the
   edit-window but it will be scanned in the background and all its
   contents (e.g. methods and variables) are listed in the "ECB
   Methods" window (*note ECB Methods::. So you can get an overlook over
   the source without changing the buffer in the edit-window.

 * Clicking on the source file with the secondary mouse button or
   C-RETURN (*note Usage of ECB::) will open the source file in the
   other edit window.

 * Right clicking on a source file will open a popup menu where
   different operation on the item under the mouse cursor can be
   performed.


